{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place 1200 g water in mixing bowl, insert simmering basket and add short-grain rice to it.","Select a heat-resistant bowl that fits in Varoma dish (approx. Ø 20 cm top, Ø 12 cm bottom, height 9 cm) and make sure the bowl leaves some holes unobstructed so steam can circulate. Place bowl in Varoma dish and set Varoma dish in position.","Place Chinese cabbage, onions, carrot, kombu, prawns, clams and squid rings in the bowl. Sprinkle with Japanese soy sauce, sake, salt, sesame oil and 40 g water, close Varoma and steam <b>20 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>. Meanwhile, mix miso paste with 200 g water in a small bowl until dissolved and set aside.","Set Varoma aside, remove simmering basket using spatula, transfer steamed rice to a bowl and cover to keep rice warm.","Stir miso-water mixture again and add to mixing bowl. Add wakame flakes, set Varoma back in position and cook <b>15 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>. Set Varoma aside.","Add silken tofu to mixing bowl and cook <b>2 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>. Adjust seasoning to taste (see tip). Serve soup as a starter, followed by steamed seafood and rice as the main course."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["1440 g water","300 g white short-grain rice (e.g. sushi rice), rinsed and drained","60 g Chinese cabbage, cut in pieces (2 cm)","100 g onions, cut in thin slices (2 mm)","40 g carrot, cut in thin strips (2 mm)","4 slices kombu (approx. 2 cm each) (optional)","10 - 12 large raw prawns, peeled and deveined (from approx. 170 g prawns)","300 g clams, shells scrubbed,","250 g raw squid rings","75 g Japanese soy sauce (see tip)","60 g sake","1 tsp salt","2 tsp light sesame oil (10 g)","80 g miso paste","5 pinches wakame flakes, dried","200 g silken tofu, cut in cubes (1.5 cm) (optional)"]}],"id":"r90383","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-ttXCSXVj_60\/XZap29Ni6-I\/AAAAAAAAhV0\/1X3gIm0PvAcKfYaHuiVStYvQsi8wdhvkQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_DTOl-QI2PNOJVJAb.png","title":"Miso soup, Sake seafood with rice","publishedAt":"2017-07-18T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"30 g","fat":"7 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"71 g","calories":"2015 kJ \/ 478 kcal"},"usefulItems":"heat-proof bowl (approx. Ø 20 cm top, Ø 12 cm bottom, height 9 cm)","hintsAndTricks":["This combination recipe illustrates how your Thermomix®# #can be used to prepare a soup, main dish and rice all at once, resulting in clean, bright flavours and a healthy family meal.","Taste the soup before serving; if it isn’t salty enough, dissolve <b>10-20 g<b> additional miso paste in the soup.","Soy sauce comes in different strengths and flavours. The most common Japanese soy sauce is usually lighter and slightly less salty than dark Chinese soy sauce. If only dark soy sauce is available, decrease quantity to <b>50 g.<b>","Wakame and kombu (kelp) are two kinds of edible seaweed that are often used in Japanese, Korean and Chinese cuisines.","Replace soy sauce with flavoured Japanese soy sauce (e.g. kelp, dried bonito, clam), or add <b>¼ tsp<b> instant dashi powder."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","1h 5m","4 portions"]}